
[1]spousal

   SPOUSAL, a. [from spouse.] Pertaining to marriage; nuptial;
   matrimonial; conjugal; connubial; bridal; as spousal rites; spousal
   ornaments.

   SPOUSAL, n. [L. See Spouse.] Marriage; nuptials. It is now generally
   used in the plural; as the spousals of Hippolita.
